# Gemini AI Chat Application Environment Configuration
# ⚠️ SECURITY WARNING: This file is for reference only
# DO NOT include API keys or proxy settings in environment variables for production!

# ============================================================================
# APPLICATION SETTINGS (Safe for environment variables)
# ============================================================================
# Default model to use when starting the application
VITE_DEFAULT_MODEL=gemini-2.5-flash

# Request timeout in milliseconds (default: 30000)
VITE_REQUEST_TIMEOUT=30000

# Maximum retry attempts (default: 3)
VITE_MAX_RETRIES=3

# ============================================================================
# BUILD CONFIGURATION
# ============================================================================
# Environment mode (development/production)
NODE_ENV=production

# ============================================================================
# SECURITY BEST PRACTICES
# ============================================================================
# ✅ SECURE: Use application settings for sensitive data
# - API keys should ONLY be set through the app's Settings modal
# - Proxy settings should ONLY be configured in user settings
# - This keeps sensitive data out of build artifacts and source control

# ❌ DEPRECATED: Environment variables for sensitive data
# The following variables were removed for security reasons:
# - VITE_GEMINI_API_KEYS (use Settings → API Keys instead)
# - VITE_PROXY_URL (use Settings → Network → Proxy instead)

# ============================================================================
# SETUP INSTRUCTIONS
# ============================================================================
# 1. Deploy your app to Cloudflare Pages or any hosting platform
# 2. Open the deployed app in your browser
# 3. Click Settings button to configure:
#    - API Keys: Get from https://makersuite.google.com/app/apikey
#    - Proxy: Configure if needed for your network
# 4. All settings are stored securely in your browser's local storage

# ============================================================================
# WHY THIS IS MORE SECURE
# ============================================================================
# ✅ API keys never exposed in source code or build artifacts
# ✅ No risk of accidentally committing secrets
# ✅ Users control their own credentials
# ✅ Easy to update keys without redeployment
# ✅ Works with any hosting platform (Cloudflare, Vercel, Netlify, etc.)

# ============================================================================
# TROUBLESHOOTING
# ============================================================================
# If you encounter issues:
# 1. Verify API keys are valid at https://makersuite.google.com/
# 2. Check proxy settings if using corporate network
# 3. Ensure no firewall blocking Google AI API endpoints
# 4. Check browser console for detailed error messages
# 5. Clear browser storage and reconfigure if needed